Alembic migrations for the FitLens API.

Layout
  alembic.ini            Config; sqlalchemy.url is a placeholder.
  alembic/env.py         Puts `app` on sys.path, targets Base.metadata, and
                         overrides the URL with app.config.settings.database_url
                         at runtime (so DATABASE_URL controls the target DB).
  alembic/versions/      Revision scripts.

Common commands (run from apps/api with the venv active):

  # Apply all migrations to the configured database.
  .venv/bin/alembic upgrade head

  # Target a throwaway database without touching your dev DB.
  DATABASE_URL=sqlite:////tmp/fitlens_migtest.db .venv/bin/alembic upgrade head

  # Roll everything back.
  .venv/bin/alembic downgrade base

  # Generate a new revision from model changes (review the output!).
  .venv/bin/alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

SQLite uses batch mode (render_as_batch=True) so ALTER-style changes work via
the table-copy workaround. Postgres applies ALTERs directly.
